<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-04-10T13:45:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-04-10T13:45:00-05:00" n="861" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d861">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.48 Earthquake of 1931/112:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-04-10T13:00:00-05:45">April 10, 1931—1
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 6:33 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>2. Will Rogers left here this noon by special airplane for San José,
                            Costa Rica. His visit brought cheer to this saddened community and has
                            given new hope to the despondent. He has snapped us out of our
                            morbidness and has given us a saner spirit to carry on our work of
                            reconstruction. We all owe him a profound debt of gratitude.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>